  "text": "In these initial observations Pta demonstrated a combination of two distinct phenotypes that has not been reported in any AT studied so far: Pta promoted cell-cell aggregation of the bacterium and, when in interaction with the host, elicited a cytopathic effect. Both of these features have strong implications for the pathogenesis of P. mirabilis infection as this bacterium is known to form efficient biofilms on catheters that aids in the long-term persistence of the infection in the host [CITATION_1] .",
